        "text[TOK_Q_DELIM]The Medical—Vocational Rules, also known as grid rules, are guidelines used by the Social Security Administration to ensure consistency in decision-making regarding disability claims. These rules take into account a person's age, education, work experience, and physical or mental conditions to determine their ability to adjust to other work. The premise is that as a person ages, their ability to transition into new occupations diminishes, making it more likely for older individuals to be considered disabled if they cannot perform their previous work or any other work considering their limitations.[TOK_Q_DELIM]Answer": {
